The explosions that took place in #Beirut this week are heartbreaking and tragic.

My prayers are with the families that lost loved ones and the entire Lebanese community as they navigate the aftermath of this horrific incident.

retweeted_text: We would like to thank @RepRonWright for his post today about the passing of @ProjectK9Hero Ambassador, K-9 Axel. It goes to show just how special Axel was, that members of Congress publicly regonize his end of watch. We are committed to seeing the K9 Hero Act, HR5081, is passed. https://t.co/bZ0TRBEVIJ

full_text:
These brave men and women went above and beyond the call of duty to preserve our way of life, and they deserve proper recognition. 

I am proud to lead this effort in the House with @RepVeasey to ensure these heroes will never be forgotten. https://t.co/BpFAMpexvm

full_text:
Happy birthday to Joanna Troutman. 

In 1835, a Georgia Battalion traveled to Velasco, Texas, to help in the fight for Texas independence. Joanna sewed a flag to take with them and later was raised as the national flag of Texas.
 
The flag is now known as the Troutman Flag. https://t.co/32VodEVZqN

full_text:
I am proud to introduce H.R. 5081, the K-9 Hero Act. 

This legislation creates a grant program to assist nonprofits that take in retired working dogs and provide financial assistance to the owners of retired working dogs. 

Press Conference: https://t.co/sIfWDnqjEv https://t.co/kFWFvclIkU
